From c1753d518a77be2f32eca4a52c01c5e1ab71f371 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 09:36:12 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 07/28] [displayxr inline-3d #625 B4a] chrome port: shared
 component + hooks; per-element weave premise disproven

Extract the six content/shell-only weave files into a shared components/displayxr/
component (browser weave client + weaver/service mojom impls + GPU provider +
weave mojom), consumed by BOTH content_shell and the chrome target. Wire the
weave into the chrome/ layer: ChromeBrowserMainParts (deferred weave-client init
after the first window is shown), ChromeContentBrowserClient (BindGpuHostReceiver
+ AppendExtraCommandLineSwitches + DisplayXRService frame binder), and
ChromeContentGpuClient::PostCompositorThreadCreated (GPU weave provider). All
gated on --enable-inline-3d. content_shell still builds (regression vehicle).

`chrome` builds + links clean and the wiring is fully live on Leia: weave client
init, xrWeaveBindWindowEXT -> 0, GPU provider registered, isSessionSupported(
'inline-3d') true, XRDisplayLayer constructs + tags the canvas.

KEY B4 FINDING (design premise disproven): the per-element weave never fires in
chrome. The canvas never becomes a taggable SkiaRenderer TextureDrawQuad --
- a sub-page 2D OR WebGL canvas is squashed into the page content layer (no
  distinct compositing layer / quad; will-change makes a layer but still no
  canvas TextureDrawQuad);
- a full-window canvas is drawn via the overlay/root path (zero DrawTextureQuad
  calls);
- the whole web-contents reaches SkiaRenderer as ONE ~1800x1200 kTextureContent
  quad.
So Seam B (tag + substitute at SkiaRenderer::DrawTextureQuad) does not match how
chrome composites canvas elements (squash-into-page or DComp overlay). Checkpoint
+ pause for a Seam-B redesign (likely the OverlayProcessorWin / DCLayerOverlay
path). Diagnostic evidence in docs/roadmap/webxr-step-b-design.md.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
